title: Two crashes cause delays on I-66 eastbound in Prince William County
text:
Two crashes along the eastbound side of Interstate 66 in Prince William County are causing backups.

It’s not immediately known if anyone was seriously hurt in the crashes.

Multi-Vehicle Crash. I-66 EB past VA-234 (Exit 44/Prince William Pkwy). Prince William County, Virginia. Two left lanes are blocked with 2 right lane getting by. Delays begin before VA-234, 1 mile. — MATOC Alerts (@MATOC) October 8, 2019

Both of the incidents happened near the Prince William Parkway, and transportation officials said delays are building.

AD
description: Traffic is backed up near the Prince William Parkway along I-66 east.
